description: This file declares external API functions related to the Ansc Ato Protocol Object, including creation, removal, enrollment, and initialization functions.

methods.name: AnscCreateAtoProto
methods.description: Creates and returns a handle to a new Ato Protocol Object, given container, owner, and reserved handles.

methods.name: AnscAtoProtoCreate
methods.description: Creates a new Ato Protocol Object instance with specified context and owner handles.

methods.name: AnscAtoProtoRemove
methods.description: Removes and cleans up the specified Ato Protocol Object instance.

methods.name: AnscAtoProtoEnrollObjects
methods.description: Enrolls necessary objects into the Ato Protocol Object instance.

methods.name: AnscAtoProtoInitialize
methods.description: Initializes the Ato Protocol Object instance.
